This is, of course, from Pope’s Essay on Man. One knows not what to wonder at more: Pope’s not finding a monosyllable to replace “hero” (for example, “man”) so as to accommodate the definite article before the next word, or Shade’s replacing an admirable passage by the much flabbier final text. Or was he afraid of offending an authentic king? In pondering the near past I have never been able to ascertain retrospectively if he really had “guessed my secret,” as he once ob